"  <div id=\"topicText\">",
"   <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H12047318\">",
"    <span class=\"h1\">",
"     INTRODUCTION",
"    </span>",
"    &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;The following material represents a subset of chemotherapy regimens that are used for the treatment of patients with advanced renal cell cancer.",
"    <strong>",
"     This is",
"    </strong>",
"    <strong>",
"     not an exhaustive list.",
"    </strong>",
"    Additional regimens may be added over time, particularly as treatment for renal cell cancer evolves.",
"   </p>",
"   <p>",
"    This topic review does not address the appropriate context for use of these regimens in the care of patients with renal cell cancer. Clinicians should refer to the individual disease-oriented topic reviews that discuss the use of these protocols in appropriate clinical situations:",
"   </p>",
"   <p>",
"    <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"     <li>",
"      (See",
"      <a class=\"medical medical_review\" href=\"UTD.htm?27/32/28170?source=see_link&amp;anchor=H27#H27\">",
"       \"Anti-angiogenic and molecularly targeted therapy for advanced renal cell carcinoma\", section on 'Temsirolimus'",
"      </a>",
"      .)",
"     </li>",
"    </ul>",
"   </p>",
"   <p>",
"    These tables are provided as examples of how to administer these regimens; there may be other acceptable methods. All protocols must be administered by clinicians who are trained in the use of chemotherapy. The clinician is expected to use his or her independent medical judgment in the context of individual circumstances to make adjustments, as necessary.",
"   </p>",
"   <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H12047343\">",
